text.section:
To be eligible for a policy issued under this subtitle, a person must:
be domiciled in the State;
own, lease, or rent a primary place of residence in the State and, regardless of the person's domicile, reside in the State for more than 1 year;
maintain a main or branch office or warehouse facility in the State, and base and operate motor vehicles intrastate in the State;
have filed as a State resident for income tax purposes; or
have a nonresident permit issued under § 13-402.1(e) of the Transportation Article.
